# image-processing / pillow

Pillow (PIL Fork) is the de-facto Python imaging library — deterministic, scriptable
image creation and manipulation driven entirely from Python code. A `.py` script
renders headlessly to a raster image file (PNG/JPEG/WebP/...) with no GUI or display
dependency, which makes it a clean fit for OOTA's version-controllable authoring model.

controls do
  image-processing.title: { label: "Title", type: "text" }
  image-processing.width: { label: "Width (px)", type: "range" }
  image-processing.height: { label: "Height (px)", type: "range" }
  image-processing.bg: { label: "Background", type: "color" }
  image-processing.fg: { label: "Foreground", type: "color" }
end

## Required reading
- [Pillow official documentation](https://pillow.readthedocs.io/en/stable/) — python-pillow project; canonical API reference and handbook/tutorial. License: MIT-CMU (HPND/PIL).
- [image-processing skill (jezweb/claude-skills)](https://github.com/jezweb/claude-skills/blob/main/plugins/design-assets/skills/image-processing/SKILL.md) — community plugin; ships an `img-process` CLI plus Pillow-script generation for resize/crop/convert/thumbnail/OG-card/watermark workflows.
- [Claude Cookbook — image crop tool (multimodal)](https://platform.claude.com/cookbook/multimodal-crop-tool) — Anthropic official cookbook; Pillow-backed crop tool for better image analysis.

## Render
```bash
pip install pillow
python render.py
# verify
file out.png   # -> PNG image data, ... 8-bit/color RGB, non-interlaced
```

## Failure modes
- Output bytes drift across Pillow/libjpeg/freetype versions — pin `pillow==12.2.0`
  for byte-stable renders.
- System fonts are non-deterministic — bundle a TTF/OTF in-repo and load via
  `ImageFont.truetype`, not the default `ImageFont.load_default`.
- Pillow emits raster only — no SVG/vector output. Use a different tool for scalable
  markup.
- Prefer PNG as the canonical artifact (lossless, deterministic); JPEG/WebP encoders
  may vary by build.
- No `Image.show()` / display calls in the render script — keep it headless.
